        " businessmen, office workers, teachers, and others from nearly every walk of life. Most people quickly learned that open opposition was dangerous since Gestapo informants and agents were widespread. Yet a significant number of them still worked against the National Socialist government.     During May 1935, the Gestapo broke up and arrested members of the Markwitz Circle , a group of former socialists in contact with ": null
